3.1 Categorical predictors

FEV %>% 
  select(Sex, Smoker, FEV) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-FEV) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(value, FEV, fill = value)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free")

3.2 Numeric predictors

FEV %>% 
  select(Age, Height, FEV) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-FEV) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(value, FEV)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method= lm) + 
  facet_wrap(~name, scales = "free")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

4 Modelling

4.1 Model 1

M1 <- lm(FEV ~ Height + Sex + Smoker + Age, data = FEV)
gglm(M1)

4.2 Box-Cox

MASS::boxcox(M1)

4.3 Model 2

M2 <- lm(log(FEV) ~ Height + Sex + Smoker + Age, data = FEV)
gglm(M2)
